  "finding": "The syscall diagnostic refutes a simple network syscall-count explanation for the remaining nested TLS gap. ylong_http_client does not issue materially more recvfrom/sendto calls than libcurl in this traced HTTPS-over-HTTPS-proxy run. The dominant traced difference is runtime scheduling/timer shape: ylong records far more futex, clock_nanosleep, epoll_wait, and sched_yield activity. Because strace distorts timings, this is a narrowing signal only; the next implementation-level hypothesis should focus on ylong_base runtime/timer/speed-controller interaction around response reads rather than CONNECT parsing, TLS cipher choice, or raw network syscall count.",
